@startuml CursorTopology
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ranksep 120
skinparam nodesep 80

left to right direction

title Cursor CLI Topology — Policy-Gated Autonomous Loop

actor "Human" as Human
actor "Cursor CLI\n(agent)" as Cursor

package "Harness Layer" as Harness {
  component "entrypoint.sh\n(docker)" as Entrypoint <<script>>
  component ".env loader\nCURSOR_API_KEY check" as EnvLoader <<logic>>
  component "smoke-test mode" as Smoke <<mode>>
  component "steering detection\nAGENTS.md | CLAUDE.md | .cursor/rules" as Steering <<prompt>>
  component "proveo-loop.mdc seed\n(opt-in: CURSOR_SEED_RULES=1)" as LoopRule <<prompt>>
}

package "Native Policy Layer" as Policy {
  component "cli-config.json\npermissions.deny\n(survives --force)" as Deny <<config>>
  component "/etc/cursor/hooks.json\nenterprise shell-audit hook\n(root-owned, immutable)" as Hooks <<security>>
  component "readonly subagents\n@adversarial-reviewer\n@security-reviewer" as Subagents <<subagent>>
}

package "Execution Loop" as Loop {
  component "Spec / Goal" as Spec <<step>>
  component "Plan + Acceptance Criteria" as Plan <<step>>
  component "Implement (edit)" as Implement <<step>>
  component "Verify (run tests/lint)" as Verify <<step>>
  component "Inspect Failure → Adjust" as Inspect <<step>>
}

package "Container Sandbox" as Sandbox {
  component "agent --force --sandbox disabled\n(Docker is the sandbox)" as Force <<flag>>
  component "/app workspace mount\nruns as host uid (non-root)" as Mounts <<storage>>
  component "network egress layer\nopen | proxy | firewall" as Net <<security>>
}

cloud "Cursor backend\napi5.cursor.sh (inference)\napi2.cursor.sh (API / auth)" as Backend

Human --> Entrypoint : starts container
Entrypoint --> EnvLoader
Entrypoint --> Smoke
Entrypoint --> Steering : report, never write
Entrypoint --> Cursor : " exec ""agent --force"" "
Cursor --> Steering : reads project rules
Cursor --> Loop : executes loop
Loop --> Verify : runs detected commands
Verify -> Inspect : on failure
Inspect -> Plan : next iteration
Cursor --> Deny : every tool call checked
Cursor --> Hooks : shell requests audited\n(NDJSON)
Cursor --> Subagents : in-loop review gates
Cursor -[#00BAC6,dashed,bold]-> Backend : inference (vendor-pinned)
Net ..> Backend : provider pin = "".cursor.sh""
Force --> Sandbox : within\ncontainer boundary
LoopRule ..> Steering : when\nopted in

note right of Policy
Native policy survives ""--force"":
deny rules beat allow, enterprise hooks
beat project hooks. The harness owns
""/etc/cursor/hooks.json"" (root-owned);
the project owns "".cursor/*"".
Audit hook is fail-open by design —
enforcement lives in deny rules + egress.
end note

note right of Sandbox
Outer boundary identical to claudecode:
container + egress modes. Cursor adds an
in-process policy layer, but ALL inference
transits the Cursor backend — no local
model / custom base-URL escape hatch,
so ""--local-model"" does not apply here.
end note

Net .> Force : network containment\noffsets full consent

@enduml
